Footage of the incident, which took place in the Egyptian city of Tanta, was uploaded to YouTube and has been watched more than 50,000 times in three days.

When the video begins, the lion that is about to launch the attack can be seen sitting on a stool on the left-hand side of the shot - with two more of the big cats also in the ring.

In the blink of an eye, the animal lunges towards the circus owner - dramatically flooring her. 

Amazingly, Ms El-Helw was able to get up and was led to safety while another circus worker coaxed the lions back into their cages.

